It’s a reprieve for small scale farmers as government disburses 1.4 billion shillings to settle the outstanding payment of maize farmers. Speaking ahead of the inaugural of Arid and Semi Arid Lands Conference, Devolution Cabinet Secretary Eugene Wamalwa reiterated that the vetting process of legitimate farmers is expected to kick off today at various depots in the country. https://www.youtube.com/edit?o=U&video_id=yeJ-XrGevrs